WEBVTT

00:03:29.012 --> 00:03:32.000
but the company that held the patents
threatened to sue the lab

00:03:32.024 --> 00:03:33.206
for patent infringement.

00:03:33.230 --> 00:03:34.389
So as a result,

00:03:34.413 --> 00:03:37.275
for 2 years, no test was available.

00:03:38.291 --> 00:03:39.441
During that time,

00:03:39.465 --> 00:03:42.715
Abigail died of undiagnosed long QT.

00:03:43.776 --> 00:03:47.013
Gene patents clearly were a problem
and were harming patients.

00:03:47.467 --> 00:03:49.873
But was there a way
we could challenge them?

00:03:50.266 --> 00:03:51.998
Turns out that the Supreme Court

00:03:52.022 --> 00:03:55.136
has made clear
through a long line of cases,

00:03:55.160 --> 00:03:57.946
that certain things
are not patent eligible.

00:03:58.925 --> 00:04:01.299
You can't patent products of nature --